# LaTeX build output, except the compiled PDFs themselves, which are committed
# on purpose so the book is readable without a LaTeX toolchain (see CLAUDE.md's
# "Compiling chapters" and "The subject index" sections). Regenerate these with
# pdflatex/makeindex rather than hand-editing them.
*.aux
*.toc
*.idx
*.ind
*.ilg
*.log
*.dvi
*.out

# Raw datasets downloaded by capstone-chapter notebooks (large binaries; the
# notebook re-downloads them automatically from their public source on demand).
ch16_data/

# Synthetic data generated by chapter notebooks' own simulation code (fully
# reproducible from the fixed random seed in the notebook; not downloaded from
# anywhere, so there is nothing to commit).
ch12_data/

# SyncTeX editor-sync byproducts (regenerated per-machine/editor; not build output anyone else needs).
*.synctex.gz

# Instructor's solutions to the chapter-end Suggested Exercises, and their companion
# notebooks (English and Chinese). These are answer keys, not manuscript content, and
# stay local only rather than being pushed to the public repo.
solutions_chapter_end_questions/
solutions_chapter_end_questions_zh/

# Chinese edition: kept as local working files only, not tracked or pushed from this
# point forward. (Origin/main still has an older, partial ch.1-6 Chinese translation
# from before this rule was added; see CLAUDE.md / commit history for that history.)
ai_in_finance_zh.tex
ai_in_finance_zh.pdf
chapters_zh/
notebooks_zh/
